  "text": "Since we did not observe in any of our in-vitro experiments fictive walking, 562 namely, a motor output that resembled a functional walking gait, we have to conclude 563 that, in the locust, functional inter-leg coordination during walking is only accomplished 564 by way of complementary sensory inputs or descending commands from the brain. This 565 was also reported for many other walking systems [CITATION_1] and vast 566 evidence suggests that sensory inputs plays a major role in walking coordination (e.g. 567 [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . 568",
